\c 38
\s1 Mazmur yang ditulis Daud, meminta agar Allah tidak melupakannya
\q1
\v 1 Ya TUHAN, [jangan menegurku walaupun Engkau marah/janganlah menegur aku dalam amarah-Mu], atau [menghukumku dalam murka-Mu/walaupun Engkau murka jangan menghukum aku.]
\q1
\v 2 Engkau seolah-olah melepas panah-Mu yang melukai tubuhku,
\q2 [dan tangan-Mu menghantam aku hingga terjatuh/ dan tangan-Mu seolah-olah memukul aku jatuh.]
\q1
\v 3 Sekujur tubuhku [kesakitan/terasa sangat sakit] karena kemarahan-Mu.
\q1 Kesehatanku telah dirampas,
\q2 karena dosaku.
\q1
\v 4 Dosa-dosaku bagaikan banjir yang membuatku tenggelam,
\q2 Seperti beban berat, aku tidak [kuat/kuasa] menanggung dosaku.
\b
\q1
\v 5 Karena [kebodohanku/aku telah bertindak bodoh], luka-lukaku bernanah dan berbau busuk.
\q1
\v 6 Aku tertunduk malu dan hancur,
\q1 Sepanjang hari aku berkabung.
\q1
\v 7 Aku dipenuhi rasa malu,
\q2 dan sekujur tubuhku berasa sakit.
\q1
\v 8 Aku lemah dan hancur;
\q2 aku merintih karena am very distressed in my inner being, and I groan with pain.
\b
\q1
\v 9 Yahweh, you know the that I desire \add to be healed\add*;
\q2 you hear me while I am groaning.
\q1
\v 10 My heat pounds heavily, and all my strength is gone.
\q2 I am no longer able to see well.
\q1
\v 11 My friends and neighbors stay away from me because of my sores;
\q2 even my own family stays far from me.
\q1
\v 12 And those who want to kill me set traps to catch me;
\q2 those who want to harm me discuss the ways that they can get rid of me;
\q2 they plot against me all day.
\b
\q1
\v 13 Now I act like a deaf man, and do not listen \add to what theysay\add*.
\q2 I act like a man who cannot talk, and I say nothing \add to reply tothem\add*.
\q1
\v 14 I act like a man who does not answer \add when people talk tohim\add*,
\q2 because he cannot hear anything.
\q1
\v 15 But Yahweh, I trust in you.
\q2 My Lord God, you will answer me.
\q1
\v 16 I said to you, “Do not cause \add me to die, with the resultthat\add* my enemies will rejoice!
\q2 Do not cause me to stumble, with the result that they will be very happy!”
\b
\q1
\v 17 I say that because I am about to fall down,
\q2 and I constantly have pain.
\q1
\v 18 I confess the wrong things that I have done;
\q2 I am very sorry for the sins that I have committed.
\q1
\v 19 My enemies are healthy and strong;
\q2 there are many people who hate me for no reason.
\q1
\v 20 Those who do evil things to me in return for my doing good things to them
\q2 oppose me because I try to do what is right.
\b
\q1
\v 21 Yahweh, do not abandon me!
\q2 My God, do not stay far from me!
\q1
\v 22 Lord, you are the one who saves/rescues me;
\q2 Quickly \add come and\add* help me!